2500|$|In August 2004, Time {{magazine}} {{named the}} city one of Europe's 14 [...] "secret capitals" [...] where Bergen's capital reign is acknowledged within maritime businesses and {{activities such as}} aquaculture and marine research, with the Institute of Marine Research (IMR) (the second-largest oceanography research centre in Europe) as the leading institution. Bergen is the main base for the Royal Norwegian Navy (at Haakonsvern) and its international airport Flesland is the main heliport for the Norwegian North Sea oil and gas industry, from where thousands of <b>offshore</b> <b>workers</b> commute to their work places onboard oil and gas rigs and platforms.|$|E
