50|$|During the 1970s {{the company}} {{developed}} survival suits for <b>offshore</b> oil <b>workers</b> in the North Sea. In 1980 the company's breathable, waterproof fabric system, called Helly Tech, was launched. Helly Tech garments use both hydrophilic and microporous technology. Hydrophilic garments have water-loving molecular chains which pass water vapor to the outside. Microporous garments have tiny pores that allow water vapor {{to pass out}} of the fabric without letting rain droplets in.|$|R
